{
  "texts": [
    "7 compares image-to-voxel aggregation methods for overcoming the limitations of voxel-based encoding.",
    "Prior works adopt Spatial Cross-Attention (SCA) [32,38,48] to distribute image features across all voxel grids, providing slight improvements.",
    "However, spatial misalignment between voxel and image space often leads to hallucinated mappings [22], and the lack of explicit supervision on what to extract and where to place it results in suboptimal performance.",
    "In contrast, Query-guided Aggregation (QueryAgg) explicitly extracts dynamic object features and selectively integrates them into the voxel regions they occupy.",
    "This targeted aggregation strategy mitigates hallucinations, reduces unnecessary computation, and yields a +2.76 mIoU gain on dynamic objects and +1.53 overall, while maintaining high efficiency with 83.3 ms latency and 2,788 MB memory."
  ]
}